{
  "stem": "16571.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my sister was left for dead.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When the Russians came in, they found her swollen, double her size, her legs and everything else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they took her to hospital, and they brought her round, and she survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I learned now that I got brother and I've got a sister.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then a--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I learned that through letter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, 20 months later.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't know-- didn't know that anybody survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never went home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of my friends went back to Poland, and back to their countries and-- to see whether anybody lived.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never went home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was too stupid, too young, didn't even think about it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we found that my sister, the young sister who lived away from home-- remember me telling you at the beginning of the film?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mmm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She came home one day and told my father she was engaged.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was only about 17.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The way I see it, my father said, yes, over my dead body.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So back-- back she went, to this aunt she was staying with in another part of-- two or three villages-- two or three towns away.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "About 14 or 18 got themselves together and they call themselves halutzim, and they run across the border to Russia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Russians caught them, and they kept them in prison for three months as spies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When they quizzed them and found out that they were only children, they didn't-- they were not spies, [INAUDIBLE] my sister finished up working all through the war in a-- in a Russian hospital, scrubbing and do that and the other.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She finished up-- They found-- They found that she finished up in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She met her husband in Vienna, and they had-- and they had a lovely marriage.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
